  "text": "Reasoner et al. [CITATION_1] and Gupta et al. [CITATION_2] , who used fentanyl for procedural sedation, also found no significant difference in hemodynamic parameters between their study groups. However, increased mean arterial pressure and heart rate relative to baseline were observed in the latter study, probably due to",
